Don't worry. It's what I do.

00:49:58.850 --> 00:50:00.477
I heard what happened to Lord Hong.

00:50:01.269 --> 00:50:02.103
I'm truly sorry.

00:50:13.782 --> 00:50:15.325
Can you go on living?

00:50:21.748 --> 00:50:23.458
It won't be like before.

00:50:24.125 --> 00:50:25.669
You've lost your world.

00:50:29.756 --> 00:50:32.133
That's why I'm dying too.

00:50:33.718 --> 00:50:35.428
I offer my deepest condolences.

00:50:44.229 --> 00:50:45.272
Are you Gil-dong?

00:50:45.856 --> 00:50:47.566
We need Gil-dong's name.

00:50:47.649 --> 00:50:49.734
You're the one who needed the name of…

00:50:51.152 --> 00:50:52.153
It's nice to meet you…

00:50:53.822 --> 00:50:55.448
Gil-dong.

00:50:59.578 --> 00:51:01.997
Who are you?

00:51:02.414 --> 00:51:05.083
I'm a mother
whose son was taken away by the king.

00:51:05.917 --> 00:51:09.671
I'm an orphan
whose family was taken away by the king.

00:51:09.754 --> 00:51:12.883
I'm a father
whose daughter was taken away.

00:51:14.301 --> 00:51:16.553
I'm a child whose sibling was taken away.

00:51:17.178 --> 00:51:19.973
I'm an old monk
whose friend was taken away.

00:51:20.932 --> 00:51:23.310
I'm a subject
whose loyalty was taken away.

00:51:28.064 --> 00:51:30.901
We have all lost our worlds.

00:51:37.866 --> 00:51:39.034
The palace.

00:51:42.787 --> 00:51:44.623
Your Majesty,

00:51:44.706 --> 00:51:47.292
please reconsider your decision!

00:51:47.375 --> 00:51:48.376
Royal Confucian Academy.

00:51:48.460 --> 00:51:51.087
Please reconsider your decision!

00:51:52.631 --> 00:51:54.549
Markets. Schools.

00:51:55.300 --> 00:51:56.718
In every corner of this kingdom,

00:51:57.177 --> 00:51:59.137
there are people like you.

00:52:14.653 --> 00:52:18.531
Where will Gil-dong's name be used?

00:52:19.407 --> 00:52:23.620
His name will represent the people
worn down by poverty and oppression.

00:52:27.958 --> 00:52:30.126
And what is the purpose?

00:52:31.336 --> 00:52:32.671
It is

00:52:32.754 --> 00:52:35.423
to take down the one on the throne.

00:52:36.257 --> 00:52:37.842
The throne?

00:52:39.803 --> 00:52:41.179
Does that mean…

00:52:44.307 --> 00:52:45.225
A revolt.

00:52:47.560 --> 00:52:49.312
That's how it will be recorded in history

00:52:49.813 --> 00:52:51.898
if we fail.

00:52:55.485 --> 00:52:57.988
Gil-dong is nothing more
than a petty thief.

00:52:58.071 --> 00:52:59.489
He cannot represent the people.

00:53:00.031 --> 00:53:01.992
The return of Im Kkeok-jeong's spirit.

00:53:02.075 --> 00:53:03.243
The great thief.

00:53:03.326 --> 00:53:04.619
A beast with monstrous strength.

00:53:04.703 --> 00:53:06.454
A legendary hermit. An immortal being.

00:53:06.538 --> 00:53:08.498
They're nothing but false rumors.

00:53:08.581 --> 00:53:09.916
They're dreams.

00:53:11.668 --> 00:53:13.169
And they're hopes.

00:53:17.632 --> 00:53:19.050
Gil-dong always came by

00:53:19.134 --> 00:53:20.844
whenever I was hungry and sick,

00:53:20.927 --> 00:53:23.638
although I don't know how he always knew.

00:53:25.015 --> 00:53:26.850
So each time he came by,

00:53:26.933 --> 00:53:28.685
the warmth he left behind
made me so happy.

00:53:28.768 --> 00:53:30.311
Gil-dong!

00:53:31.312 --> 00:53:34.065
It seems like Gil-dong
is looking after us as well.

00:53:34.733 --> 00:53:37.902
There is nowhere in Joseon

00:53:37.986 --> 00:53:40.780
that Gil-dong's hands cannot reach!

00:53:44.784 --> 00:53:47.037
"A friend on the road"?

00:53:47.120 --> 00:53:48.663
Is that what it means?

00:53:51.624 --> 00:53:53.543
If the one who sits on the throne changes,

00:53:55.712 --> 00:53:57.964
will the world change?

00:53:58.798 --> 00:54:00.925
Yesterday, my son died.

00:54:01.593 --> 00:54:03.928
Today, your father died.

00:54:04.929 --> 00:54:07.599
Tomorrow, it could be
your mother and brother.

00:54:08.224 --> 00:54:09.225
And then,

00:54:10.060 --> 00:54:11.352
you could be next.

00:54:15.607 --> 00:54:18.443
At the very least,
we will be able to change tomorrow

00:54:18.526 --> 00:54:20.278
and the days that follow.

00:54:41.466 --> 00:54:44.052
Did you expect Gil-dong's refusal?

00:54:45.595 --> 00:54:47.347
She will return,

00:54:47.847 --> 00:54:49.474
to continue her life.

00:54:55.313 --> 00:54:58.483
Before that, we must find a way
to approach the king's bedchamber.

00:54:59.400 --> 00:55:02.445
We must find out
what's going on in the palace.

00:55:29.139 --> 00:55:30.265
You're back.

00:55:31.766 --> 00:55:34.936
His Majesty woke up.
Inform Her Majesty at once!

00:55:35.019 --> 00:55:36.563
Yes, my lady.

00:55:42.861 --> 00:55:44.070
Where are you going?

00:55:45.738 --> 00:55:47.782
Assemble the State Tribunal.

00:55:55.081 --> 00:55:57.458
This traitor attempted
to assassinated His Majesty.

00:55:57.542 --> 00:55:59.711
- Seize him!
- Yes, sir!

00:56:00.795 --> 00:56:02.172
What's this about?

00:56:02.714 --> 00:56:03.631
Your Highness!

00:56:06.009 --> 00:56:08.553
His Majesty is now questioning
Hong Min-jik's eldest son.

00:56:16.895 --> 00:56:20.190
I know nothing about it, Your Majesty!

00:56:20.273 --> 00:56:23.276
The State Tribunal
inspected the area thoroughly

00:56:23.359 --> 00:56:24.819
before the royal procession arrived.

00:56:25.403 --> 00:56:26.863
Do you still deny it?

00:56:26.946 --> 00:56:30.700
How does that make me the assassin?

00:56:30.783 --> 00:56:32.076
Throughout all of Joseon,

00:56:32.160 --> 00:56:35.705
there is but one archer
who can strike a target

00:56:35.788 --> 00:56:37.332
from five ri.

00:56:41.085 --> 00:56:42.295
Who is it?

00:56:46.674 --> 00:56:47.842
That was…

00:56:51.179 --> 00:56:52.889
my father.

00:57:04.234 --> 00:57:06.444
And who inherited his blood?

00:57:14.786 --> 00:57:16.120
I don't hear any answer.

00:57:16.204 --> 00:57:17.664
Twist his legs.

00:57:17.747 --> 00:57:18.998
Yes, Your Majesty.

00:57:19.707 --> 00:57:20.833
Stop!

00:57:34.639 --> 00:57:36.099
What are you doing?

00:57:36.182 --> 00:57:37.559
You're here.

00:57:38.893 --> 00:57:42.355
I'm looking for the man
who nearly took your life.

00:57:42.855 --> 00:57:44.232
I already found him.

00:57:49.779 --> 00:57:51.281
He's standing in front of me.

00:58:01.583 --> 00:58:03.126
Say that again.

00:58:03.501 --> 00:58:04.877
All these tragedies

00:58:06.296 --> 00:58:08.172
began with Your Majesty.

00:58:31.154 --> 00:58:32.155
Say that again.

00:58:33.698 --> 00:58:35.074
It's Your Majesty's fault.

00:58:38.077 --> 00:58:38.911
Say that again.

00:58:38.995 --> 00:58:40.288
Your Majesty!

00:58:42.081 --> 00:58:43.249
It's your fault.

00:58:56.971 --> 00:58:58.097
Mother.

00:58:59.057 --> 00:58:59.974
What's the matter?

00:59:01.017 --> 00:59:02.268
Young Master…

00:59:08.149 --> 00:59:10.109
- What are you going to do?
- Let go of me.

00:59:10.693 --> 00:59:11.861
Just stay here.

00:59:11.944 --> 00:59:13.863
With no proof,
he'll be freed after the torture.

00:59:13.946 --> 00:59:15.448
Because of me--

00:59:16.157 --> 00:59:17.241
What's wrong?

00:59:30.963 --> 00:59:32.256
Hong Eun-jo!

00:59:42.600 --> 00:59:44.727
That's the person you see?

01:00:02.453 --> 01:00:03.579
Young Master.

01:00:04.664 --> 01:00:06.374
This is the last time I'm asking.

01:00:07.166 --> 01:00:08.543
Say that again.

01:00:29.981 --> 01:00:31.607
Does this mean Hong Eun-jo is now…

01:00:35.361 --> 01:00:36.779
No.

01:01:17.487 --> 01:01:20.782
{\an8}There will be no more mistakes?

01:01:20.865 --> 01:01:21.741
{\an8}Who is it?

01:01:21.824 --> 01:01:24.452
{\an8}Who hid behind you and stood in my way?

01:01:24.535 --> 01:01:25.620
{\an8}Was it you?

01:01:26.162 --> 01:01:27.872
{\an8}Were you behind everything?

01:01:27.955 --> 01:01:29.373
{\an8}Don't take this the wrong way.

01:01:29.457 --> 01:01:31.959
{\an8}I just want to see
if my body is all right.

01:01:32.043 --> 01:01:35.338
{\an8}Why does everything
have to be so cruel to us?

01:01:35.421 --> 01:01:37.882
{\an8}Hong Min-jik's death
has shaken the ministers.

01:01:37.965 --> 01:01:40.134
{\an8}It seems like the decision has been made.

01:01:40.218 --> 01:01:42.970
{\an8}It was also the late king's wish.

01:01:43.054 --> 01:01:44.597
{\an8}You'll be in danger if you stay here.

01:01:44.680 --> 01:01:45.973
Let's run away.

